		<div id="comment_body_64448378"><p><div class="quote"><p>Try to pip install --user pkg. If it exists as a deb the pip commend will fail.</p></div><p>This is true of all system Python in GNU/Linux distributions since <a href="https://peps.python.org/pep-0668/" title="python.org">PEP 668</a> [python.org]. Ostensibly, it's to protect the user from installing a new major version of a package whose breaking changes cause other packages installed on the system to stop working. Creating a venv solves the problem.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64448378">

</div>
</div>

