		on Saturday May 04, 2024 @09:32PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23312556&amp;cid=64448438">#64448438</a>)
		<small><a href="https://linktr.ee/flowerpt" title="https://linktr.ee/flowerpt" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a>
<a href="//slashdot.org/~bill_mcgonigle/journal/" title="Thursday April 15, 2010 @07:30PM" class="user_journal_display">Journal</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64448438"><p>Ubuntu is a weird borkage of Debian which was mostly obsoleted by Bookworm's inclusion of firmware.</p><p>Unless you need automatic ZFS support in the installer then install Bookworm.</p><p>There's a ZFS howto that just needs a LiveCD image. The lxqt image works better than GNOME.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64448438">
